title: Glenn Maxwell dropped by Yorkshire for disciplinary reasons, says coach Jason Gillespie | The
text:
Australia all-rounder Glenn Maxwell was left out of the Yorkshire Vikings’ final Twenty20 match of the season for ‘disciplinary reasons.’
“It was just unprofessional behaviour and I don’t wish to add anything further. It has been dealt with and we have moved on and the slate is clean. As soon as the decision was made we cracked on,” said Yorkshire coach Jason Gillespie.
The World Cup star was originally meant to join the Australia ‘A’ team for its tour of India, but extended his contract with Yorkshire after compatriot Aaron Finch was ruled out for the rest of the season.
